USESETUPVARS vary_atomic_frac
IF vary_atomic_frac
  PPDEFINE VARY_ATM_FRAC
  D rt_vary_atomic_frac allow for varying atomic weight?
  PARAMETER rt_vary_atomic_frac BOOLEAN False
  D atmu atomic weight 
  VARIABLE atmu
ENDIF

D rt_ion_min Minimum ionization fraction tracked by IHA_SPEC,IHP_SPEC
PARAMETER rt_ion_min REAL 1e-8

D rt_neutral_min Minimum neutral fraction tracked by IHA_SPEC,IHP_SPEC
PARAMETER rt_neutral_min REAL 0.0

D rt_ion_threshold  Convergence threshold for radiation + ionization fraction
D & subcycling.  Used to advance radiation until photo-ionization bubbles
D & reach a rough steady state.  This rad/ionize subcycling effectively
D & compensates for too-large radiation timesteps, and so enables
D & (radiation,ionization,heat/cool) dt to be roughly the hydro dt.
D & WARNING, rt_ion_threshold must be relatively large compared to rt_ion_min,
D & or else the code will subcycle ionization unphysically, and may advance
D & radiation + ionization too far ahead in time.
# Should probably be the same as the minimum ionization or less,
# since you can't otherwise resolve the minimum ionization (you might
# overshoot then get corrected back above the converged solution).
# UPDATE: behavior has changed, not clear that comment about being same as
# minimum ionization or less applies - AT, 2019 May 01
PARAMETER rt_ion_threshold REAL 1e-1
